'''''As of February 2006, the information on this page is no longer correct. Wikipedia's current [[Lucene]] index does not use "stop words", so any word can be successfully used in search queries.'''''
----
Some words in wikipedia cannot currently be [[wikipedia:searching|searched]] for, because they are deemed too common. The following is a full list of those words. They are written as links, so that at least articles with a single common word as title can be found through this list.
If the exact title of an article is known or guessed, the '''Go''' button can be used; this feature is not affected by the above-mentioned restriction.
Further articles which are difficult to find otherwise: *Years: [[1]] [[2]] [[3]] [[4]] [[5]] [[6]] [[7]] [[8]] [[9]]
*[[E.T. the Extra-Terrestrial|E.T.]] *[[Just Like That]]
